        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 5:01PM PDT by NWS Portland OR</headline>
        <description>At 500 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Waldo Lake, or 20 miles east of Oakridge, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Waldo Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
